<div class="highlight">
<strong>Distance:</strong> 12.0 km loop<br>
<strong>Time:</strong> ~4 h 30 min<br>
<strong>Elevation gain:</strong> 640 m
</div>

<p>This backcountry circuit climbs from the Yumoto Onsen area through quiet conifer forest to a pair of pristine crater lakes tucked high in the mountains. Lake Kirikomi dazzles with cobalt water framed by volcanic ridgelines, while Lake Karikomi sits in a peaceful basin ringed by marsh grasses and alpine flowers.</p>

<p>Boardwalks protect the fragile wetlands around the lakes, and the trail often rewards hikers with sightings of native deer and migratory birds. The descent loops past bubbling hot spring vents before returning to Lake Yunoko&apos;s shoreline.</p>

